---
title: Fall Harvest Kale Salad with Brussels Sprouts, Delicata Squash & Dijon Dressing
description: Cooler weather always makes us think about…salad! Seriously, this robust salad will give you all the cozy fall feels. We toss tender kale with roasted Brussels sprouts and delicata squash, chewy dried cranberries, and a creamy, tangy honey Dijon dressing. It’s all topped with Parmesan cheese and walnuts for a hearty-yet-light-feeling dinner you’re going to want to make all year round.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/fall-harvest-kale-salad-7e1d25d6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/fall-harvest-kale-salad-63208c01ad5f4c8aaa0aa737-31426c7b.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 43 g
  protein: 14 g
  fiber: 13 g
  sodium: 440 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fall-harvest-kale-salad-63208c01ad5f4c8aaa0aa737
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise (quarter any larger sprouts). Halve
@delicata squash{1} lengthwise; scoop out seeds with a #spoon{} and discard. Slice
crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Remove and discard any large stems from
@kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve @lemon{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts and squash on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}
and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast
on top and middle racks.) Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Let cool at least ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add kale and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} to a large #bowl{}; using your
hands, massage until leaves are tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> TIP: Don't skip this step—massaging helps make kale's texture more salad-friendly.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @dried cranberries{1%ounce},
@water{1%tbsp}, and juice from lemon. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until
softened, ~{1%minute}. Transfer cranberries to a #plate{}, reserving lemon juice
mixture in bowl.

To bowl with lemon juice mixture, add @Dijon mustard{4%tsp}, @maple syrup{2%tbsp},
@olive oil{1%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp}. Whisk to combine. Season with salt and pepper
to taste.

To bowl with kale, add roasted veggies, drained cranberries, half the Dijon dressing,
and half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}. Gently toss to combine. Season with salt and
pepper.

Divide salad between plates or shallow bowls. Drizzle with remaining Dijon dressing;
garnish with @walnuts{1/2%ounce} and remaining Parmesan. Serve.